\subsubsection{Model Architecture}

The architecture comprises three component types: a shared plant model, per-loop controller models, and a specialised cooling loop model.

\paragraph{GRUPlant.}
The plant model is a MIMO encoder-decoder GRU network. The encoder processes the CV input window concatenated with a learned scenario embedding $\mathbf{e}_s \in \mathbb{R}^{32}$, producing a hidden state that encodes the current plant operating condition. The decoder autoregressively generates PV predictions step-by-step: at each timestep $t$, the previous PV vector and the target-window CV are concatenated and passed through the GRU decoder cell, followed by a two-layer fully connected head that maps the hidden state to all five PV outputs simultaneously:

\begin{equation}
    \hat{\mathbf{y}}_t = \text{FC}\!\left(\text{GRU}_\text{dec}\left([\mathbf{x}_t^{cv},\, \hat{\mathbf{y}}_{t-1}],\, \mathbf{h}_{t-1}\right)\right), \quad t = 1, \ldots, T
\end{equation}

The scenario embedding conditions the encoder on the operating regime (normal, AP\_no, AP\_with, AE\_no), allowing a single model to distinguish attack dynamics without separate instances per scenario.

\paragraph{GRUController.}
One controller model is instantiated per control loop (PC, LC, FC, TC). Each follows a seq2seq encoder-decoder structure: the encoder reads the loop's input history — setpoint (SP), process variable (PV), and three causally-ordered auxiliary sensor channels — and compresses it into a hidden state. The decoder autoregressively predicts the control variable (CV) sequence over the target horizon, feeding its own previous output as input at each decoding step.

The three base signals per loop are extended with three additional causal channels selected from the physics-informed causal graph: the L0 parent (DCS logic: sensor $\rightarrow$ actuator), L1 parent (direct physical effect), and L2 parent (two-hop ripple effect), bringing each controller's input to six features. The causal channels are appended at runtime using the plant-level scaler without re-fitting. Table 2 summarises the full input configuration per loop.

